    <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  To orchestrate a chain of format-specific converters, applying the first suitable one to a given file, so the caller does not need to know which converter handles which format. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This class allows to convert any document into the predefined list of formats according to the available list of converters. The list of converters is set via the class constructor. The first suitable converter is used (the one whose method :meth:<computeroutput>~dedoc.converters.AbstractConverter.can_convert</computeroutput> returns True), \ so the order of converters is important. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
